274
00:36:44.611 --> 00:36:46.989
Ribs and a leg badly broken.

275
00:36:49.442 --> 00:36:51.444
Do you understand my words?

276
00:36:55.211 --> 00:36:57.147
Where is this?

277
00:36:57.391 --> 00:36:59.619
You're at
the Priory of St. Clement.

278
00:36:59.644 --> 00:37:01.063
We're a place for you to heal.

279
00:37:02.088 --> 00:37:03.714
Wha... What town?

280
00:37:04.515 --> 00:37:05.850
There is no town.

281
00:37:07.667 --> 00:37:09.419
Do you know the story of Saul?

282
00:37:11.520 --> 00:37:12.831
What?

283
00:37:13.061 --> 00:37:16.207
It goes. there once
was a man. Saul...

284
00:37:16.232 --> 00:37:19.569
a breather of menaces
against disciples of the Lord.

285
00:37:20.329 --> 00:37:22.140
He came to the Prince of Priests

286
00:37:22.165 --> 00:37:24.560
and asked of him
letters into Damascus.

287
00:37:24.585 --> 00:37:25.979
to the synagogues.

288
00:37:26.004 --> 00:37:27.357
That if he came across

289
00:37:27.382 --> 00:37:29.277
any man or woman of this life.
he should lead them bound

290
00:37:29.301 --> 00:37:30.677
and...

291
00:37:32.451 --> 00:37:34.453
That is all we need to do.

292
00:37:35.146 --> 00:37:36.689
Just a few drops.

293
00:37:39.273 --> 00:37:41.067
It was not too painful?

294
00:37:43.017 --> 00:37:44.268
It were not.

295
00:37:48.780 --> 00:37:50.073
I'm Sister Brigid.

296
00:37:51.257 --> 00:37:52.676
What's your name?

297
00:37:54.785 --> 00:37:55.995
Randolph.

298
00:38:00.358 --> 00:38:03.027
Well. I owe you
an apology. Randolph.

299
00:38:03.688 --> 00:38:05.190
What apology?

300
00:38:07.322 --> 00:38:09.241
You begged for me
to let you die.

301
00:38:11.231 --> 00:38:12.523
And I did not.

302
00:38:14.793 --> 00:38:15.855
You said it was right.

303
00:38:15.880 --> 00:38:17.131
I were with fever.

304
00:38:19.320 --> 00:38:21.114
Well. your fever has passed.

305
00:38:22.524 --> 00:38:23.935
Rest now. Randolph.

306
00:38:47.290 --> 00:38:50.418
Your body
is covered in scars.

307
00:39:07.424 --> 00:39:09.760
Do you mean anyone
at this Priory harm?

308
00:39:13.753 --> 00:39:14.963
I do not.

309
00:39:25.154 --> 00:39:28.199
Will any harm
follow you here?

310
00:39:29.928 --> 00:39:31.221
It will not.

311
00:39:40.416 --> 00:39:43.336
You will do them no harm.

312
00:40:15.646 --> 00:40:17.792
Now back to the bed.

313
00:40:32.717 --> 00:40:34.135
Now back to the door.

314
00:41:02.315 --> 00:41:03.981
Now open the door.

315
00:41:22.689 --> 00:41:24.273
Go as far as you'd like.

316
00:43:12.177 --> 00:43:14.072
William. careful. please.

317
00:43:22.365 --> 00:43:23.605
Can you row yet?

318
00:43:26.331 --> 00:43:28.434
There is a boat
on the west shore.

319
00:43:30.920 --> 00:43:32.171
That's all right.

320
00:43:33.505 --> 00:43:35.983
You can stay here
if you help in the orchard.

321
00:43:36.008 --> 00:43:38.010
Oh. I'm... not a farmer.

322
00:43:38.871 --> 00:43:40.498
Then you know not how to hunt.

323
00:43:40.949 --> 00:43:42.409
Aye. I know how to hunt.

324
00:43:43.683 --> 00:43:46.537
There is some game
on this island.

325
00:43:46.562 --> 00:43:50.167
But no. you cannot hunt.
You cannot even draw a bow.

326
00:43:50.192 --> 00:43:52.844
-I can draw my bow.
-It's mostly rabbits.

327
00:43:52.869 --> 00:43:55.622
-Do you know how to trap?
-I know how to trap.

328
00:43:56.923 --> 00:43:59.068
Good. But no more than six traps

329
00:43:59.093 --> 00:44:01.095
or the population
will not sustain.

330
00:44:01.743 --> 00:44:03.287
Can you manage six traps?

331
00:44:07.954 --> 00:44:09.414
I can manage six traps.

332
00:44:11.386 --> 00:44:12.429
Good.

333
00:44:13.961 --> 00:44:16.839
Then the rest of your time.
you may help in the orchard.

334
00:44:52.961 --> 00:44:54.754
Are you
trying to flee?

335
00:44:58.793 --> 00:45:00.087
You are quiet.

336
00:45:01.772 --> 00:45:03.941
I am quiet and slow.

337
00:45:05.389 --> 00:45:08.951
You are quiet.
but you need to be slow.

338
00:45:08.975 --> 00:45:10.120
You're a cripple.

339
00:45:10.144 --> 00:45:11.853
Aye. you're a leper.

340
00:45:12.771 --> 00:45:16.501
It is all right
to be slow. We are safe here.

341
00:45:16.525 --> 00:45:19.171
That's quite a thing
to say. You know that?

342
00:45:19.195 --> 00:45:21.256
I know that
because she has made us safe.

343
00:45:21.280 --> 00:45:22.656
Oh. your Prioress?

344
00:45:25.035 --> 00:45:26.328
She were like us.

345
00:45:27.369 --> 00:45:31.457
She knew great sorrow.
Great pain.

346
00:45:32.121 --> 00:45:33.372
Widowed young.

347
00:45:35.488 --> 00:45:37.008
But through that sorrow.

348
00:45:37.033 --> 00:45:39.219
she found the strength
to heal us.

349
00:45:39.244 --> 00:45:41.847
Well. you do not look
like you've been healed.

350
00:45:45.324 --> 00:45:47.501
The Prioress once told me
a story

351
00:45:47.526 --> 00:45:49.528
of a great philosopher...

352
00:45:50.340 --> 00:45:53.010
the greatest philosopher
of his time.

353
00:45:54.001 --> 00:45:57.398
But one day.
his king turned against him.

354
00:45:57.423 --> 00:46:00.509
Threw him in a dungeon
to be tortured and executed.

355
00:46:01.867 --> 00:46:03.930
But in his misery.

356
00:46:03.955 --> 00:46:07.059
when he had nothing.
an angel came

357
00:46:07.084 --> 00:46:09.336
to the philosopher
and she spoke to him.

358
00:46:10.454 --> 00:46:12.307
And from her.

359
00:46:12.332 --> 00:46:14.936
he learned
that it did not matter

360
00:46:14.961 --> 00:46:17.546
if this whole world
were misery...

361
00:46:19.356 --> 00:46:21.400
if all he had were death.

362
00:46:23.015 --> 00:46:25.035
Because he had one thing

363
00:46:25.060 --> 00:46:27.395
that could never be
touched or taken.

364
00:46:29.914 --> 00:46:31.248
He had his mind.

365
00:46:33.110 --> 00:46:34.361
And in his mind...

366
00:46:36.165 --> 00:46:37.499
he had God.

367
00:46:40.122 --> 00:46:43.666
It's never too late
to find peace.

368
00:46:44.489 --> 00:46:45.840
What are you doing?

369
00:46:45.864 --> 00:46:48.801
Ah.
I row across every day.

370
00:46:48.825 --> 00:46:50.720
Your friend was strong enough
to take you.

371
00:46:50.745 --> 00:46:52.621
but some are not.
so I ferry them.

372
00:46:52.663 --> 00:46:55.390
-Will you take me across?
-I will not.

373
00:46:55.415 --> 00:46:58.519
You can row yourself
when you're stronger.

374
00:46:58.544 --> 00:47:01.398
For now. work at your tasks.
Trapping. I hear.

375
00:47:01.423 --> 00:47:03.675
-I will hunt.
-No. you can't hunt.

376
00:47:09.083 --> 00:47:10.685
Leper.

377
00:47:10.710 --> 00:47:13.130
what happened
to that great philosopher?

378
00:47:13.943 --> 00:47:16.946
He were tortured
and executed. of course.

379
00:47:18.320 --> 00:47:19.362
Of course.

380
00:47:25.895 --> 00:47:28.457
♪ Sumer is icumen
In loude sing cuccu! ♪

381
00:47:28.482 --> 00:47:30.835
♪ Groweth seed
and bloweth meed ♪

382
00:47:30.860 --> 00:47:33.359
♪ And springth the wode now ♪

383
00:47:33.384 --> 00:47:35.529
♪ Sing cuccu ♪

384
00:47:35.554 --> 00:47:38.697
♪ Ewe bleteth after lamb
Loweth after calve cow ♪

385
00:49:20.023 --> 00:49:22.293
Oi! Oi!

386
00:49:22.318 --> 00:49:24.361
The Leper has brought someone!

387
00:49:24.865 --> 00:49:26.617
From the far shore!

388
00:50:06.509 --> 00:50:07.845
Papa's dead.

389
00:51:23.187 --> 00:51:24.730
How's the girl?

390
00:51:38.180 --> 00:51:40.182
Let me show you
my trees.

391
00:51:50.523 --> 00:51:53.710
These are the elderberries.

392
00:51:53.735 --> 00:51:56.506
They harvest late in the summer.

393
00:51:56.531 --> 00:51:58.372
Do they know
what you were before this?

394
00:51:58.397 --> 00:52:00.583
Oh. you'll have
to favor this side

395
00:52:00.608 --> 00:52:01.776
for my hearing.

396
00:52:04.390 --> 00:52:07.142
Pears. I harvest just after.

397
00:52:10.061 --> 00:52:12.124
And what were I before this?

398
00:52:12.149 --> 00:52:13.876
Oh. a sell sword at best.

399
00:52:13.901 --> 00:52:16.279
Aye. at best. certainly.

400
00:52:17.327 --> 00:52:18.703
We have a way about us!

401
00:52:20.004 --> 00:52:21.482
You remember the trees?

402
00:52:21.507 --> 00:52:23.967
-Pears and elderberries.
-Wonderful.

403
00:52:26.700 --> 00:52:27.993
Some of them know.

404
00:52:29.482 --> 00:52:32.693
But the Prioress does not care
who we were.

405
00:52:34.770 --> 00:52:37.232
And the apples harvest
in the autumn.

406
00:52:38.650 --> 00:52:41.737
Did she. uh.
speak of what happened to her?

407
00:52:43.386 --> 00:52:45.449
Well. the Prioress
is tending to the girl.

408
00:52:45.473 --> 00:52:48.351
You should speak with her.
if you are concerned.

409
00:52:51.639 --> 00:52:52.890
What were the trees?

410
00:52:54.825 --> 00:52:57.245
Pears. apples
and elderberries.

411
00:52:59.150 --> 00:53:00.360
Wonderful.

412
00:53:11.996 --> 00:53:13.830
This will be
your last letting.

413
00:53:15.365 --> 00:53:17.576
Though your body
still has much healing.

414
00:53:21.248 --> 00:53:22.332
You're tired.

415
00:53:23.447 --> 00:53:24.490
I am.

416
00:53:25.997 --> 00:53:27.499
But I have been tired before.

417
00:53:29.482 --> 00:53:31.124
The child does not sleep.

418
00:53:34.478 --> 00:53:35.855
What happened to her?

419
00:53:37.454 --> 00:53:39.130
Terrible things.

420
00:53:41.964 --> 00:53:45.152
-She told you her story?
-No. she does not speak.

421
00:53:45.177 --> 00:53:47.429
She does not eat
and she does not sleep.

422
00:53:54.906 --> 00:53:56.241
What is her name?

423
00:54:03.961 --> 00:54:05.213
Margaret.

424
00:54:08.195 --> 00:54:09.487
Who is she?

425
00:54:11.639 --> 00:54:14.558
I met her father. A farmer.

426
00:54:15.816 --> 00:54:17.586
Well. he's dead.

427
00:54:17.611 --> 00:54:18.671
It seems.

428
00:54:18.974 --> 00:54:20.411
And the mother?

429
00:54:20.436 --> 00:54:23.290
-Ah. I think dead.
-How?

430
00:54:23.315 --> 00:54:25.400
I don't know. Dead past.

431
00:54:26.119 --> 00:54:27.120
Slain?

432
00:54:28.411 --> 00:54:29.453
Perhaps.

433
00:54:34.937 --> 00:54:36.313
You lie very well.

434
00:54:45.813 --> 00:54:47.107
Did the child see?

435
00:54:49.606 --> 00:54:51.066
She could have.

436
00:54:53.773 --> 00:54:55.796
That is much for a child to see.

437
00:55:05.590 --> 00:55:07.050
I'm sorry for your friend.

438
00:55:11.644 --> 00:55:12.854
Thank you.

439
00:55:14.305 --> 00:55:16.515
Would you like me
to pray for him?

440
00:55:20.549 --> 00:55:21.967
As you wish.

441
00:55:25.465 --> 00:55:26.591
What was his name?

442
00:55:31.210 --> 00:55:32.294
Edward.

443
00:55:34.606 --> 00:55:35.900
Edward.

444
00:55:39.094 --> 00:55:40.654
Be not your heart afraid.

445
00:55:40.679 --> 00:55:41.907
for ye believe in God

446
00:55:41.956 --> 00:55:43.290
and ye believe in me.

447
00:55:45.189 --> 00:55:48.025
In the house of my father.
there are many rooms.

448
00:55:49.412 --> 00:55:52.474
And when I make ready
for you a place.

449
00:55:52.499 --> 00:55:54.835
I shall come
and take thee to myself.

450
00:55:56.030 --> 00:55:59.033
For where I am. He may be also.

451
00:56:01.357 --> 00:56:03.567
And whither I go.
He shall know the way.

452
00:56:24.921 --> 00:56:26.394
-She has a knife.
-Margaret!

453
00:56:26.418 --> 00:56:27.813
She stabbed me!

454
00:56:28.097 --> 00:56:29.598
Margaret!

455
00:56:31.847 --> 00:56:33.867
It's all right.

456
00:56:35.060 --> 00:56:37.247
Margaret. it's...
it's all right.

457
00:56:37.272 --> 00:56:39.272
Margaret. it's all right.

458
00:56:42.593 --> 00:56:44.279
She don't know
this island.

459
00:56:44.304 --> 00:56:46.014
There are boar about.

460
00:56:48.492 --> 00:56:50.055
-Margaret!
-Margaret!

461
00:56:50.079 --> 00:56:51.890
Margaret!

462
00:56:51.915 --> 00:56:54.811
-Margaret!
-Margaret!

463
00:56:54.836 --> 00:56:56.378
Margaret!

464
00:58:41.937 --> 00:58:43.147
Oi.

465
00:58:45.694 --> 00:58:46.737
Oi!

466
00:58:55.165 --> 00:58:56.333
Give it.

467
00:59:09.990 --> 00:59:11.241
Give it.

468
00:59:28.547 --> 00:59:30.214
Those men that hurt you.

469
00:59:33.503 --> 00:59:35.016
do they know you're here?

470
00:59:40.129 --> 00:59:41.130
Hmm.

471
00:59:48.173 --> 00:59:49.550
What's my name?

472
00:59:55.382 --> 00:59:56.737
Say my name.

473
00:59:58.774 --> 01:00:00.025
Randolph.

474
01:00:05.466 --> 01:00:06.717
That's right.

475
01:00:12.049 --> 01:00:13.801
Who's Little John?

476
01:00:16.151 --> 01:00:19.620
That name is nonsense
and you should never speak it.

477
01:00:19.645 --> 01:00:22.248
And if you speak it.
a cat will come in the night

478
01:00:22.273 --> 01:00:23.375
and take your tongue.

479
01:00:33.327 --> 01:00:34.412
It's all right.

480
01:00:37.498 --> 01:00:38.707
Go to sleep.

481
01:00:46.235 --> 01:00:47.966
I'll watch the storm.

482
01:00:51.804 --> 01:00:53.889
All right. lay down.

483
01:00:57.726 --> 01:00:58.978
Close your eyes.

484
01:01:04.192 --> 01:01:05.234
You can sleep.

485
01:01:10.489 --> 01:01:11.782
Sleep.

486
01:01:50.279 --> 01:01:52.448
Thank you
for bringing her back.

487
01:01:54.825 --> 01:01:56.077
It were nothing.

488
01:02:01.415 --> 01:02:03.928
Do you know the story
of this Priory?

489
01:02:04.585 --> 01:02:05.836
No.

490
01:02:08.172 --> 01:02:10.067
Well. in ages before history.

491
01:02:10.091 --> 01:02:11.693
this was a holy site

492
01:02:11.717 --> 01:02:13.665
of the ancient Druids.

493
01:02:15.263 --> 01:02:17.181
They worshipped unknown gods.

494
01:02:18.891 --> 01:02:20.743
Worshipped in these woods.

495
01:02:21.978 --> 01:02:24.456
Then the Romans came long ago.
and they sensed

496
01:02:24.480 --> 01:02:25.790
the magic of this place.

497
01:02:25.814 --> 01:02:27.868
so they built their temples.

498
01:02:29.360 --> 01:02:31.130
And people upon people
sensed it.

499
01:02:31.154 --> 01:02:33.156
and they came here to worship.

500
01:02:34.646 --> 01:02:36.374
Countless gods.
tribe after tribe.

501
01:02:36.399 --> 01:02:39.235
who would not even know
how to speak to each other.

502
01:02:40.496 --> 01:02:42.819
Yet we were all
pulled to this place.

503
01:02:44.792 --> 01:02:47.420
Do you believe
there is magic in this island?

504
01:02:49.923 --> 01:02:51.590
I believe there is power in it.

505
01:02:54.427 --> 01:02:56.637
I have seen
the power in stories.

506
01:02:59.307 --> 01:03:02.601
They can be used to make men
do terrible things.

507
01:03:03.686 --> 01:03:07.648
And then those terrible things
become stories.

508
01:03:08.903 --> 01:03:10.113
And stories...

509
01:03:14.363 --> 01:03:15.364
No.

510
01:03:16.240 --> 01:03:17.741
You cannot trust any of them.

511
01:03:18.655 --> 01:03:20.491
We cannot be trusted with them.

512
01:03:22.783 --> 01:03:25.576
Knives cut bread
as well as they do flesh.

513
01:03:27.460 --> 01:03:29.128
It's a question of balance.

514
01:03:30.004 --> 01:03:31.714
Does balance have a say?

515
01:03:34.258 --> 01:03:36.677
I think if balance
did not have some say.

516
01:03:37.646 --> 01:03:39.107
we would not be here.

517
01:03:41.461 --> 01:03:45.298
This world would not...
be here and...

518
01:03:46.645 --> 01:03:48.772
we would not be
sharing these words.

519
01:03:49.834 --> 01:03:51.252
And do you ever consider that?

520
01:03:53.378 --> 01:03:55.064
The incredible precision
of balance

521
01:03:55.089 --> 01:03:57.591
over such an expanse of time.

522
01:03:59.245 --> 01:04:03.475
The balance it takes to create
a word. any specific word.

523
01:04:03.500 --> 01:04:06.336
That can pass
between lips and...

524
01:04:08.077 --> 01:04:10.370
be understood by two minds.

525
01:04:17.781 --> 01:04:19.074
Randolph.

526
01:04:22.975 --> 01:04:24.268
Thank you.

527
01:05:30.021 --> 01:05:31.814
-Mmm. Mmm.
-Mmm.

528
01:05:43.194 --> 01:05:44.236
Not hungry?

529
01:05:46.297 --> 01:05:47.464
No?

530
01:06:20.166 --> 01:06:21.668
I'll be dying soon.

531
01:06:23.357 --> 01:06:24.400
How do you know?

532
01:06:26.957 --> 01:06:28.918
I can feel it inside.

533
01:06:31.408 --> 01:06:33.243
What does it feel like?

534
01:06:35.364 --> 01:06:37.033
It feels right.

535
01:06:48.574 --> 01:06:50.117
There's someone there.

536
01:06:52.921 --> 01:06:54.915
The waters
have been busy.

537
01:06:58.328 --> 01:06:59.622
Start around the feet.

538
01:06:59.902 --> 01:07:01.111
Little cuts.

539
01:07:01.449 --> 01:07:03.134
Good. Other one.

540
01:07:04.666 --> 01:07:06.918
All right. Oh.

541
01:07:08.979 --> 01:07:10.188
Okay.

542
01:07:10.751 --> 01:07:12.312
Good.

543
01:07:12.337 --> 01:07:14.064
Right. now.
let's do down the front.

544
01:07:14.127 --> 01:07:15.921
Right down on the belly. Good.

545
01:07:16.689 --> 01:07:18.709
Right. Give me.

546
01:07:18.960 --> 01:07:20.896
Right. Watch this one.

547
01:07:20.921 --> 01:07:23.650
Just like... just like that.

548
01:07:23.675 --> 01:07:25.344
That's it. You do the other one.

549
01:07:26.734 --> 01:07:29.087
That's it. that's it. that's it.

550
01:07:29.112 --> 01:07:30.113
Pull.

551
01:08:05.808 --> 01:08:08.102
You are a brave
young man.

552
01:08:08.815 --> 01:08:10.458
Thank you. sister.

553
01:08:11.980 --> 01:08:13.357
Are you hungry. Arthur?

554
01:08:17.401 --> 01:08:18.920
I am. sister.

555
01:08:18.945 --> 01:08:21.591
Well. Sarah will fix you up
a good supper tonight.

556
01:08:21.616 --> 01:08:23.993
Herring stew. Herring stew.

557
01:08:25.847 --> 01:08:28.785
-Do you like that?
-Yes.

558
01:08:28.810 --> 01:08:30.228
Where do you come from. Arthur?

559
01:08:34.205 --> 01:08:35.891
My family farm toward Keswick.

560
01:08:35.916 --> 01:08:38.061
-Toward Keswick?
-Yes. Sir.

561
01:08:38.086 --> 01:08:40.981
-Randolph.
-Randolph. Toward Keswick.

562
01:08:41.006 --> 01:08:43.008
The Leper said
you seek your niece.

563
01:08:43.834 --> 01:08:45.680
-I do.
-You were set upon?

564
01:08:47.875 --> 01:08:49.419
-I was.
-On the road?

565
01:08:50.943 --> 01:08:52.170
Yes.

566
01:08:52.195 --> 01:08:53.947
-You are safe here.
-Which road?

567
01:08:56.023 --> 01:08:57.484
The road to Keswick. Sir.

568
01:08:59.221 --> 01:09:00.949
Thank the Lord you survived.

569
01:09:00.974 --> 01:09:02.327
I do thank the Lord.

570
01:09:02.352 --> 01:09:04.162
How about honeyed pears
after supper

571
01:09:04.187 --> 01:09:05.648
for being so brave?

572
01:09:08.501 --> 01:09:10.753
-Thank you. sister.
-Good.

573
01:09:24.259 --> 01:09:25.510
Little Margaret.

574
01:09:27.119 --> 01:09:28.638
That man. Arthur.

575
01:09:28.663 --> 01:09:31.500
Did you ever see him
before you came to the Priory?

576
01:09:34.953 --> 01:09:35.954
Margaret.

577
01:09:43.129 --> 01:09:47.047
The men...
The men who hurt your papa.

578
01:09:49.436 --> 01:09:51.063
Did you see their faces?

579
01:09:52.329 --> 01:09:53.872
Papa said to run.

580
01:10:04.710 --> 01:10:06.332
Papa stopped praying.

581
01:10:07.992 --> 01:10:09.095
He was angry.

582
01:10:10.747 --> 01:10:12.166
He prayed in his mind.

583
01:10:15.209 --> 01:10:16.499
What's Papa's name?

584
01:10:20.869 --> 01:10:22.205
Your papa's your papa.

585
01:10:34.932 --> 01:10:36.142
Bring it here.

586
01:10:45.588 --> 01:10:47.903
Oh. this is fine work.

587
01:10:51.924 --> 01:10:53.301
Oh.

588
01:10:53.503 --> 01:10:55.616
You see it favors a bend here.

589
01:10:57.059 --> 01:11:00.812
Oh. aye. Now you have to
balance it so it bends evenly.

590
01:11:02.032 --> 01:11:05.828
So this part here needs
to be thinned. All right?

591
01:11:11.065 --> 01:11:12.524
Can you make for me?

592
01:11:15.301 --> 01:11:16.719
You want me to make you a bow?

593
01:11:21.221 --> 01:11:22.263
All right.

594
01:11:30.472 --> 01:11:31.993
Today.
I remembered a story

595
01:11:32.017 --> 01:11:34.370
by a poet named Lucretius.

596
01:11:36.228 --> 01:11:38.469
He wrote on
what are called atoms.

597
01:11:40.070 --> 01:11:42.006
Where if you pick apart
the trees

598
01:11:42.031 --> 01:11:43.842
and people and stones.

599
01:11:43.867 --> 01:11:47.305
these would be the smallest
invisible pieces

600
01:11:47.330 --> 01:11:50.917
that make up
everything in creation.

601
01:11:53.017 --> 01:11:57.479
And these atoms are sailing
through the void and...

602
01:12:00.144 --> 01:12:01.955
well. sometimes.
for no reason at all.

603
01:12:01.980 --> 01:12:03.314
they change their course.

604
01:12:06.263 --> 01:12:08.474
The least amount.
not even a hair.

605
01:12:13.393 --> 01:12:17.272
And if it weren't
for that small...

606
01:12:17.999 --> 01:12:21.979
unpredictable change
forcing the atoms to cross

607
01:12:22.004 --> 01:12:23.964
and weave with each other...

608
01:12:27.100 --> 01:12:29.936
nothing at all
under the heavens would exist.

609
01:15:13.905 --> 01:15:15.924
Yes. Good.

610
01:15:16.302 --> 01:15:17.720
Harder.

611
01:15:17.745 --> 01:15:19.393
That's it. Good.

612
01:15:22.539 --> 01:15:24.749
That's good. Harder.

613
01:15:25.410 --> 01:15:26.845
Let me help you.

614
01:15:28.373 --> 01:15:30.056
Grab that one.

615
01:15:30.912 --> 01:15:33.197
Good. There we go!

616
01:15:33.221 --> 01:15:34.518
Good.

617
01:15:37.725 --> 01:15:39.493
Which one do you think
for your bow?

618
01:15:40.145 --> 01:15:41.586
Let's hold and look.

619
01:15:42.447 --> 01:15:43.448
Okay.

620
01:15:44.254 --> 01:15:46.357
There we go. They're both good.

621
01:15:57.578 --> 01:15:59.306
Margaret!

622
01:15:59.330 --> 01:16:00.932
Margaret! Come and play!

623
01:16:41.414 --> 01:16:42.415
Arthur.

624
01:16:43.791 --> 01:16:45.352
Do you know how to trap?

625
01:16:45.376 --> 01:16:47.062
-Yes.
-Good.

626
01:16:47.086 --> 01:16:49.130
I need a strong hand. Come.

627
01:17:02.268 --> 01:17:03.936
Does your family have land?

628
01:17:05.646 --> 01:17:06.646
Yes.

629
01:17:08.691 --> 01:17:10.307
How many
of you are there?

630
01:17:12.112 --> 01:17:13.539
I don't know.

631
01:17:20.286 --> 01:17:21.686
Are you all right?

632
01:17:23.244 --> 01:17:24.846
I am. I am.

633
01:17:24.871 --> 01:17:27.117
Just not as young
as I once were.

634
01:17:29.629 --> 01:17:31.214
I could use a hand up is all.

635
01:17:36.051 --> 01:17:37.262
Thank you.

636
01:17:38.888 --> 01:17:40.931
Oh aye. they delivered you
quite a blow.

637
01:17:42.933 --> 01:17:44.508
-Yes.
-Who did it?

638
01:17:46.854 --> 01:17:48.106
A man.

639
01:17:48.131 --> 01:17:49.607
Some men.

640
01:17:50.769 --> 01:17:52.970
-Bandits.
-A man. bandits?

641
01:17:53.819 --> 01:17:55.758
-Yes.
-Huh. May I look?

642
01:18:01.619 --> 01:18:03.472
It's quite a blow.

643
01:18:03.496 --> 01:18:06.975
Oh. you're lucky you survived.
You're a lucky boy.

644
01:18:06.999 --> 01:18:08.059
Yes.

645
01:18:08.083 --> 01:18:10.354
You should be thankful
to be alive.

646
01:18:10.378 --> 01:18:12.672
-Yes.
-He used a quarterstaff?

647
01:18:18.969 --> 01:18:20.322
Hmm.

648
01:18:20.346 --> 01:18:22.265
Lucky it didn't
take your head off.

649
01:18:27.019 --> 01:18:28.688
Randolph.

650
01:18:31.441 --> 01:18:32.692
Randolph.

651
01:18:35.583 --> 01:18:36.626
Moshe?

652
01:18:40.366 --> 01:18:43.077
The Prioress said to come.

653
01:19:24.619 --> 01:19:26.829
Are you in great pain?

654
01:19:35.738 --> 01:19:37.952
Do you remember the trees?

655
01:19:40.369 --> 01:19:42.371
Pears. apples and elderberries.

656
01:19:44.823 --> 01:19:46.075
Wonderful.

657
01:19:56.662 --> 01:19:59.849
You know that you are
the most important person

658
01:19:59.874 --> 01:20:01.668
in Little Margaret's life.

659
01:20:02.151 --> 01:20:05.112
Ah. I'm not important.

660
01:20:17.632 --> 01:20:19.029
Think of all the people

661
01:20:19.054 --> 01:20:20.973
whose lives you've crossed.

662
01:20:24.359 --> 01:20:27.153
We were important somehow
to all of them.

663
01:20:34.650 --> 01:20:37.778
Do you know the story
of Guy of Gisborne

664
01:20:39.774 --> 01:20:41.316
and Robin Hood?

665
01:20:46.484 --> 01:20:47.778
Yes.

666
01:20:52.683 --> 01:20:55.019
They say you killed him.

667
01:20:56.934 --> 01:20:58.453
Did you really behead him?

668
01:20:58.483 --> 01:21:01.862
-You are confused. leper.
-Well. I'll not tell a soul.

669
01:21:04.684 --> 01:21:07.687
But don't lie to a man
on his deathbed.

670
01:21:10.047 --> 01:21:13.633
So. did you really behead him?

671
01:21:17.234 --> 01:21:19.545
There were no Guy of Gisborne.

672
01:21:19.570 --> 01:21:22.656
It were just one of the many
tales that passed along.

673
01:21:24.959 --> 01:21:26.544
But I beheaded other men.

674
01:21:34.387 --> 01:21:36.389
You really don't remember?

675
01:21:38.521 --> 01:21:40.790
No.

676
01:21:40.815 --> 01:21:42.777
Think about that name.

677
01:21:47.295 --> 01:21:49.673
There were a Guy of Gisborne.

678
01:21:53.420 --> 01:21:55.130
But you did not behead him.

679
01:21:58.144 --> 01:21:59.562
You cut off his ear.

680
01:22:07.302 --> 01:22:12.367
You said. in another life.
you'd share a drink with him.

681
01:22:14.674 --> 01:22:16.050
Do you remember that?

682
01:22:28.144 --> 01:22:31.355
We seem to have
found another life.

683
01:22:38.253 --> 01:22:41.149
Now.
there is one cruelty

684
01:22:41.174 --> 01:22:43.736
I would ask you
to not bring about.

685
01:22:46.181 --> 01:22:48.201
You will
guard the orchard

686
01:22:48.226 --> 01:22:50.478
until you too die.

687
01:22:53.580 --> 01:22:55.832
You will serve the Prioress...

688
01:22:57.507 --> 01:23:01.136
and the people of this Priory.
past and future.

689
01:23:05.792 --> 01:23:09.504
But at no point in that time...

690
01:23:12.074 --> 01:23:16.711
in those
good and peaceful years.

691
01:23:19.534 --> 01:23:22.930
will you tell the Prioress
who you really are.

692
01:23:29.261 --> 01:23:30.303
Why?

693
01:23:32.875 --> 01:23:34.126
Because...

694
01:23:36.074 --> 01:23:38.052
one of those nameless.

695
01:23:38.077 --> 01:23:39.345
faceless deaths

696
01:23:39.370 --> 01:23:41.414
in the shadows of your mind...

697
01:23:44.186 --> 01:23:45.938
were in another life...

698
01:23:48.775 --> 01:23:50.192
her beloved.

699
01:23:58.553 --> 01:23:59.595
Promise me.

700
01:24:04.839 --> 01:24:06.048
Robin...

701
01:24:07.893 --> 01:24:09.144
Promise me.

702
01:24:36.560 --> 01:24:44.084
♪ Sumer is icumen in
Loude sing cuccu! ♪

703
01:24:44.109 --> 01:24:47.297
♪ Groweth seed
and bloweth meed ♪

704
01:24:47.322 --> 01:24:50.968
♪ And springth the wode now ♪

705
01:24:50.993 --> 01:24:54.598
♪ Sing cuccu ♪

706
01:24:54.623 --> 01:25:01.064
♪ Ewe bleteth after lamb
Loweth after calve cow ♪

707
01:25:01.089 --> 01:25:04.902
♪ Bulloc sterteth
bucke verteth ♪

708
01:25:04.927 --> 01:25:07.781
♪ Merye sing cuccu! ♪

709
01:25:07.806 --> 01:25:14.372
♪ Cuccu. cuccu
Wel singest thou cuccu! ♪

710
01:25:14.397 --> 01:25:16.417
♪ Ne swik thou never now! ♪

711
01:25:40.869 --> 01:25:42.519
Good-bye. Brigid.

712
01:25:55.773 --> 01:25:56.941
Arthur.

713
01:25:59.232 --> 01:26:00.316
Come.

714
01:26:03.567 --> 01:26:05.707
There's a child
on the far shore.

715
01:26:07.033 --> 01:26:08.409
Perhaps it's your niece.

716
01:26:10.600 --> 01:26:12.727
The Leper said
you sought your lost niece.

717
01:26:14.348 --> 01:26:15.740
Yes.

718
01:26:15.947 --> 01:26:18.954
-Could it be her?
-We shall see.

719
01:26:57.828 --> 01:26:59.830
I do not see signs of anyone.

720
01:27:01.207 --> 01:27:02.541
Ah. we should wait.

721
01:27:03.482 --> 01:27:04.900
Maybe they will return.

722
01:27:27.057 --> 01:27:28.308
What is your name?

723
01:27:32.493 --> 01:27:33.577
Arthur.

724
01:27:34.752 --> 01:27:36.855
Do not waste time lying to me.

725
01:27:36.879 --> 01:27:38.130
What is your real name?

726
01:27:43.094 --> 01:27:44.178
Godwyn.

727
01:27:47.473 --> 01:27:49.868
You are deciding. Godwyn.

728
01:27:49.892 --> 01:27:52.061
whether to do
the deed yourself...

729
01:27:53.354 --> 01:27:54.856
or to fetch your family.

730
01:27:58.275 --> 01:27:59.211
What deed?

731
01:27:59.235 --> 01:28:01.403
How many men
have you killed. Godwyn?

732
01:28:02.905 --> 01:28:05.633
How many children
have you killed?

733
01:28:11.038 --> 01:28:14.125
I have killed so many.
I could not give you a count.

734
01:28:15.877 --> 01:28:17.730
For longer than
you've been alive.

735
01:28:17.754 --> 01:28:20.733
I've been killing the kin of
those I killed a lifetime ago.

736
01:28:20.757 --> 01:28:22.776
I do not remember the first.

737
01:28:22.800 --> 01:28:25.094
who meant nothing to me
at the time. but...

738
01:28:26.345 --> 01:28:28.365
their brothers
and their children.

739
01:28:28.389 --> 01:28:31.017
their grandchildren.
they remember me.

740
01:28:31.976 --> 01:28:34.020
So now I must kill them.

741
01:28:34.979 --> 01:28:37.499
Again and again.

742
01:28:37.523 --> 01:28:41.527
In different forms.
like shades. Again.

743
01:28:42.904 --> 01:28:45.072
And again. and it never ceases.

744
01:28:48.700 --> 01:28:50.411
It's a curse. Godwyn.

745
01:28:52.246 --> 01:28:53.891
And it's one
you bring on yourself.

746
01:28:53.915 --> 01:28:56.625
even if done through duty.

747
01:28:57.626 --> 01:28:59.628
It cares not about your duty.

748
01:29:00.421 --> 01:29:03.424
This world cares
only about blood.

749
01:29:05.176 --> 01:29:07.386
And blood is all
it will give in return.

750
01:29:10.097 --> 01:29:13.059
But do you want
to kill a child. Godwyn?

751
01:29:15.352 --> 01:29:16.955
Do you want to be responsible

752
01:29:16.979 --> 01:29:19.398
for the killing
of a little girl?

753
01:29:22.819 --> 01:29:24.028
No.

754
01:29:35.873 --> 01:29:37.374
Your father's dead?

755
01:29:38.960 --> 01:29:40.020
And your uncles?

756
01:29:43.146 --> 01:29:44.898
I am the eldest left.

757
01:29:49.516 --> 01:29:50.893
Who else yet lives. Godwyn?

758
01:29:53.417 --> 01:29:54.501
My mother.

759
01:29:56.101 --> 01:29:57.144
My aunts.

760
01:29:58.980 --> 01:30:00.582
My sisters.

761
01:30:00.606 --> 01:30:02.524
You have a home. Godwyn?

762
01:30:04.701 --> 01:30:06.452
-Yes.
-Go home.

763
01:30:07.947 --> 01:30:10.574
Tell your family
all blood debts are paid.

764
01:30:11.283 --> 01:30:13.077
They'll all be paid someday.

765
01:30:15.287 --> 01:30:16.622
Sleep in your own bed.

766
01:30:17.735 --> 01:30:19.880
Hold dear the life

767
01:30:19.905 --> 01:30:22.032
you will yet share
with your kin.

768
01:30:23.715 --> 01:30:25.425
And if you return here.

769
01:30:26.491 --> 01:30:28.052
you will have wasted this chance

770
01:30:28.077 --> 01:30:29.996
at life that I give you now.

771
01:30:31.802 --> 01:30:33.655
And I will cut your throat

772
01:30:33.680 --> 01:30:35.431
and never think of you again.

773
01:30:42.105 --> 01:30:43.148
Go now.

774
01:30:45.778 --> 01:30:47.071
And do not look back.

775
01:31:41.678 --> 01:31:43.948
I thought
you had departed.

776
01:31:53.404 --> 01:31:54.905
I am Robin the Outlaw.

777
01:31:58.904 --> 01:32:02.574
You... You need to know
that I'm a monster.

778
01:32:04.877 --> 01:32:06.336
I'm not one Randolph.

779
01:32:09.169 --> 01:32:12.422
I am the outlaw. Robin Hood.

780
01:32:27.247 --> 01:32:29.416
I'm sorry...

781
01:34:29.234 --> 01:34:30.915
Tell me I should leave.

782
01:34:33.350 --> 01:34:34.912
I will go now.

783
01:34:42.733 --> 01:34:44.026
Get in the bed.

784
01:35:04.004 --> 01:35:05.714
-Brigid...
-Lie down.

785
01:38:31.169 --> 01:38:33.421
You burned my husband alive.

786
01:38:38.867 --> 01:38:40.596
I dream that
he was already dead.

787
01:38:40.621 --> 01:38:43.374
but why else did you bar
the door?

788
01:38:47.565 --> 01:38:49.427
It felt like a lifetime

789
01:38:49.452 --> 01:38:51.997
searching the ashes of our home.

790
01:38:54.853 --> 01:38:56.776
And he looked so small.

791
01:38:58.718 --> 01:39:02.555
Curled up in the corner
with so much of him gone.

792
01:39:07.059 --> 01:39:08.332
But as much as I dream.

793
01:39:08.357 --> 01:39:09.858
I know he was alive.

794
01:39:14.864 --> 01:39:16.675
Because. until the very end.

795
01:39:16.700 --> 01:39:18.135
he had wrapped himself

796
01:39:18.160 --> 01:39:20.204
around our children.

797
01:40:07.718 --> 01:40:09.636
Randolph...

798
01:40:11.561 --> 01:40:12.812
It's me.

799
01:41:06.912 --> 01:41:09.080
People speak
of Robin Hood.

800
01:41:14.151 --> 01:41:15.736
Tell his stories.

801
01:41:21.970 --> 01:41:23.514
They're all lies.

802
01:41:27.211 --> 01:41:29.922
Lies that I told long ago.

803
01:41:32.010 --> 01:41:33.849
So that fools would...

804
01:41:35.251 --> 01:41:37.336
follow me into the dark.

805
01:41:46.595 --> 01:41:49.348
Robin.

806
01:41:54.219 --> 01:41:56.137
What have they done to you?

807
01:42:01.853 --> 01:42:03.730
Don't be afraid.

808
01:42:05.886 --> 01:42:08.556
I will rescue you
from this place.

809
01:42:10.567 --> 01:42:12.861
I'll rescue Little Margaret.

810
01:42:14.492 --> 01:42:17.661
And we're gonna start
a new life together.

811
01:42:18.371 --> 01:42:19.413
Edward...

812
01:42:23.672 --> 01:42:25.883
tell me about your wife.

813
01:42:35.669 --> 01:42:36.878
My wife.

814
01:42:39.673 --> 01:42:40.882
Margaret.

815
01:42:45.105 --> 01:42:46.315
Margaret.

816
01:42:48.692 --> 01:42:50.611
My wife. Margaret.

817
01:42:52.905 --> 01:42:54.490
Paint a portrait.

818
01:42:57.075 --> 01:42:58.452
Paint a portrait?

819
01:43:02.813 --> 01:43:04.232
She has hair...

820
01:43:06.377 --> 01:43:07.503
red like...

821
01:43:09.423 --> 01:43:11.300
the setting sun.

